   We are all used to our Money saying in god we trust. I just wonder if it would be called unconstitutional if it was In allah we trust, or any other religious reference.<br>
   I think if you can look at an issue like this from someone Elses perspective you can see how it could be...uncomfortable. <br>
    In any case taking a religious reference out of the Pledge will not Weaken the strength of our great nation, and maybe more parents can be proud of thier children reciting it. <p>           Jubiley<br>
